Package: AccumulatR
Type: Package
Title: Simulation and Likelihood Tools for Evidence-Accumulation Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Niek", "Stevenson", email = "niek.stevenson@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Tools for simulating and fitting evidence-accumulation and race
    models to behavioral data. The package is designed for workflows common in
    cognitive psychology: define a model in terms of accumulators, pooled
    channels, response rules, and timing dependencies; simulate response-time
    data; and evaluate the likelihood of observed responses under alternative
    parameter values. The user-facing interface stays in R, while the repeated
    likelihood calculations are handled in C++ for speed.
License: GPL-3
